Name: add_frame
Comment:
Move to position (linear in joint-space)

When using this command, the robot must be at a standstill or come from a movej or movel with a blend. The speed and acceleration parameters control the trapezoid speed profile of the move. Alternatively, the t parameter can be used to set the time for this move. Time setting has priority over speed and acceleration settings.

Parameters.Label: name
Parameters.Comment: name of the frame to be added. The name must not be the same as any existing world model object (frame, axis, or axis group), otherwise an exception is thrown

Parameters.Label: pose
Parameters.Comment: initial pose of the new frame

Parameters.Label: refname
Parameters.Comment: name of the world model object whose coordinate frame the pose is expressed in. If nothing is provided here, the default is the robot base frame.

Name: attach_frame
Comment:
Move to position (linear in joint-space)

When using this command, the robot must be at a standstill or come from a movej or movel with a blend. The speed and acceleration parameters control the trapezoid speed profile of the move. Alternatively, the t parameter can be used to set the time for this move. Time setting has priority over speed and acceleration settings.

Parameters.Label: child
Parameters.Comment: name of the frame to be attached. The name must not be \“world\”, \“flange\”, or \“tcp\”.

Parameters.Label: parent
Parameters.Comment: name of the object that the child frame will be attached to

When using this command, the robot must be at a standstill or come from a movej or movel with a blend. The speed and acceleration parameters control the trapezoid speed profile of the move. Alternatively, the t parameter can be used to set the time for this move. Time setting has priority over speed and acceleration settings.

Name: delete_frame
Comment: Delete the named frame from the world model.

Parameters.Label: name
Parameters.Comment: name of the frame to be deleted
